ven if their voices are silenced in the end.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aAmerican fictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican fictiony19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish fictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish fictiony19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aWomen and literaturezGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aWomen and literaturezUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aWomen entertainerszGreat Britain. 0aWomen entertainerszUnited States. 4aVoice. 4agender. 4along nineteenth century. 4anarrative fiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2018 Englishz978311060418408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2018z9783110603187oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831105586610 cprintz978311055842540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110561043423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110561043.jpg  a978-3-11-060418-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DKUb2018